<class module="batchJob" runtimeProfile="rt" qualifiedName="com.tridium.batchJob.BLocalTimeUtil" name="BLocalTimeUtil" packageName="com.tridium.batchJob" public="true" final="true">
<description>
Utility class for working around the time zone offset related limitations of&#xa; the BAbsTime framework class:&#xa; &lt;ul&gt;&#xa; &lt;li&gt;BAbsTime&#x27;s member variables include an epoch millis and a time zone object.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &lt;li&gt;BAbsTime&#x27;s string encoding contains a local time and a UTC offset, but not&#xa; a time zone identifier.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &lt;li&gt;BAbsTime.decodeFromString() uses the local time and UTC offset to correctly&#xa; restore the epoch millis member variable, but it then discards the UTC offset.  &#xa; Instead it assigns the caller NRE&#x27;s time zone to the time zone object member&#xa; variable.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &lt;li&gt;BAbsTime&#x27;s data encoding only includes epoch millis.&lt;/li&gt;&#xa; &lt;/ul&gt;&#xa; For the reasons above, it&#x27;s very difficult to know the local time for &#xa; BAbsTime objects read from bog files, and for remote BAbsTime objects accessed&#xa; using fox.&#xa;&#xa; This type isn&#x27;t really a BSimple, it just subclasses it so that it can be used&#xa; to decode BAbsTime instances from strings.
</description>
<tag name="@author">Matt Boon</tag>
